YAWL Version 6.0.0-Alpha
========================

Release Date: February 16, 2026
Release Type: Alpha (Community Preview)

Contributors:
- Sean Chatman (Library Modernization Lead & Architecture Consultant)
- Claude Code Agent Team, Anthropic (AI-Assisted Development & Code Quality Automation)

Original Authors:
- YAWL Foundation Team

Description:
This alpha release modernizes YAWL's library dependencies to their latest stable versions,
establishes comprehensive validation frameworks, and improves code quality standards to
100% HYPER_STANDARDS compliance.

Major Changes:
- 24 library updates to stable, secure versions
- Performance monitoring framework
- Production validation framework
- Zero code quality violations
- Architecture preserved and verified

Status: Alpha Release
- Intended for community review and testing
- Not recommended for production use
- Feedback welcome via GitHub issues

Next Steps:
- Beta release after community feedback
- Release candidate for production validation
- Stable 6.0.0 release

For detailed changes, see CHANGELOG.md
For technical details, see /validation/ and /performance-reports/

